olive oil
1 portion cauliflower
1 carrot
1 beetroot
1 onion
1 tbs balsamic vinegar
½ tbs water
1 tsp brown sugar
1 packet ciabatta
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet roasted almonds
1 packet creamy pesto dressing
1 bag salad leaves
1 packet romesco sauce
1 Kumara
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

Preheat oven to 240ºC/220ºC fan-forced. Cut cauliflower into small florets. Cut carrot and kumara into bite-sized chunks. Cut beetroot into small chunks. Place veggies on a lined oven tray with a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt, then toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes. Set aside to cool slightly.

TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between two trays.

While the veggies are roasting, thinly slice red onion. In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook onion, stirring, until softened, 5-6 minutes. Reduce heat to medium, then add the balsamic vinegar, water and the brown sugar and mix well. Cook until dark and sticky, 3-5 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

Meanwhile, cut or tear the ciabatta into bite-sized chunks. Place ciabatta on a second lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle over garlic & herb seasoning. Toss to coat, then sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese. Bake until golden, 5-8 minutes.

TIP: Adding enough olive oil ensures your croutons become crunchy and golden.

While the croutons are baking, roughly chop roasted almonds. In a small bowl, combine creamy pesto dressing with a splash of water. Set aside.

Add salad leaves and romesco sauce to the
roasted veggies. Toss to combine and season
to taste.

Divide romesco roast veggie salad between plates. Top with caramelised onion, garlic-herb croutons and creamy pesto dressing. Sprinkle over roasted almonds to serve.